orig=Winds for three last days SE SW WSW to SW to SSW. On 30 the 7 AM wind to NE following heavy with snow and sleet and veered by N 9 AM NW with large amounts of snow and some drift. Roads now good for sleighing. Weather mild. Has this snow storm here any cause and what cnnection with the Rocky Mountain & Missouri snow storm (as per telegram). I am strangely impressed that the storm was a [nasty] cyclone mno|Local time: mean|QC flag: passed|Image File: HarbourGrace_USSI-401_M1958_1871-11-01_OBS-L.jpg
orig=Unusual high tide no damage or danger. [Illegiible] also the appearance before the snow storm mno|Local time: mean|QC flag: passed|Image File: HarbourGrace_USSI-401_M1958_1871-11-01_OBS-L.jpg

orig=Prevaling winds NW to SW amd S and SE back again then W to NW same as last year. High winds and heavy squalls and damp. This variable nature of the winds is an interesting co-existing fact with the apparent position of the Milky Way and leads me to conclude prima fasce at all events for a similar season (the rest seems to be astronomical observations). mno|Local time: mean|QC flag: passed|Image File: HarbourGrace_USSI-401_M1958_1871-12-01_OBS-L.jpg

orig=8 days partial rain this month. These times very uncertain but frequently every late at night or every early in the morning. mno|Local time: mean|QC flag: passed|Image File: HarbourGrace_USSI-401_M1958_1871-12-01_OBS-L.jpg

orig=The cumulus cloud of mixed gray leaden and yellow color (?) very finer clous here often. In the fine days the cirius is a calleud in its beautiful form a (?) in the heavens. The amount of cloudiness in december (?) vary greatly as I can give no (?) radia of oh, save the (?) powered down as rain often and then it froze on New Years night so that there was nothing but a glitter of ice as a huge shaking throughout the whole town. mno|Local time: mean|QC flag: passed|Image File: HarbourGrace_USSI-401_M1958_1871-12-01_OBS-L.jpg
